

## Objective
Understanding why Dijkstra algorithm fails on negative weights.



## 1. What is Dijkstra’s Algorithm?

Dijkstra’s algorithm is used to find the shortest path from one node to all other nodes in a graph.

It always picks the node with the smallest distance first and assumes that distance is correct.

This works only when all edge weights are positive.



